        "id": 5,
        "type": "text",
        "name": "Text",
        "title": "Magento",
        "h1": null,
        "style": "dark",
        "decorator": "none",
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://virtocommerce.com/glossary/magento-alternatives\">Magento&#39;s</a>&nbsp;open source shopping cart solution is an option for mid-sized to large businesses, but not appropriate for a small business who just entered the world of ecommerce to start their webstore using Magento. Magento is suitable for large corporations with sufficient funds to hire programmers, as Magento requires a lot of coding. For enterprises, Magento is a viable Shopify alternative.&nbsp; Smaller companies should consider other Shopify competitors which are more appropriate for small business.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Pros</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Probably its most well known feature is its flexibility. Being open source, that means anyone using it can go into the source code and tinker with it for complete customization. It also allows for easy third party integration.</li>\n\t<li>Its large user community means you can find support for issues you have quite easily online, plus they are always developing useful plugins for it.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Cons</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>By far the biggest con of this Shopify competitor&nbsp;is its price. While the community version of it is free and can be used for small businesses, mid-tier businesses and larger enterprises have to shell out upwards of $20,000 per year according to some sources.</li>\n\t<li>While the platform does have a huge user base and a lot of people who like to tinker with it, true Magento developers -- meaning ones who completely know what they are doing -- are hard to find and are likely going to be expensive.</li>\n\t<li>Magento is going to be daunting for people who are not at least a little tech savvy, so if you don&#39;t have a dedicated IT team, this may not be the best platform to use. The loading times for the free version can be slow and hosting can be an issue (although Magento does offer cloud hosting).&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "url": {
            "urlText": "",
            "url": "",
            "style": "btn--orange btn--round"
        },
        "noTop": true,
        "noBottom": null,
        "noPad": null
